Claims Claims  What is claimed is: Claim 1 . An MRI adipose tissue mimic composition comprising 0-100% linoleic acid; 0-100% oleic acid; 0-50% palmitic acid; 0-50% stearic acid; and 0-10% polyunsaturated fatty acids. Claim 2. The adipose mimic composition of claim 1 comprising 0-100% linoleic acid; 0-100% oleic acid; and 0-10% polyunsaturated fatty acids; wherein the composition does not contain palmitic or stearic acid and is liquid at room temperature. Claim 3. The adipose tissue mimic of claim 2, comprising between 0 and 18.7% linoleic acid. Claim 4. The adipose tissue mimic of claim 2, comprising 9-10% linoleic acid; 80-90% oleic acid; and 0-10%. polyunsaturated fatty acids. Claim 5. The adipose tissue mimic of Claim 4, comprising 9-10% linoleic acid; 80-81 % oleic acid; and 9- 0% polyunsaturated fatty acids. 6. The composition of claim 1 , comprising 10-50% of palmitic acid, stearic acid, or a combination of palmitic acid and stearic acid; and wherein the composition is solid at room temperature. Claim 7. The composition of Claim 6, comprising 62% linoleic acid; 25% oleic acid; 10% palmitic acid; and 3% stearic acid; and wherein the fatty acids of the composition are of 90-99% purity. Claim 8. The composition of Claim 6, comprising 23% linoleic acid; 49% oleic acid; and 22% palmitic acid; and wherein the fatty acids of the composition are of 90-99% purity. Claim 9. An MRI calibration object, comprising a container, wherein the container is substantially filled with an adipose mimic composition comprising: 0-100% linoleic acid; 

 0-100% oleic acid; 0-50% palmitic acid; 0-50% stearic acid; and 0-10% polyunsaturated fatty acids. Claim 10. The MRI calibration object of Claim 9, wherein the container comprises a material with a magnetic susceptibility close to or equal to that of water. Claim 1 1 . The MRI calibration object of Claim 10, wherein the container comprises glass or plastic. Claim 12. The MRI calibration object of Claim 1 1 , wherein the container is substantially invisible to MRI imaging. Claim 13. The MRI calibration object of Claim 12, wherein the container comprises TEFLON (TM). Claim 14. The MRI calibration object of Claim 9, wherein the shape of the container is a sphere, cylinder, or cube. Claim 15. The MRI calibration object of Claim 9, wherein the adipose mimic composition comprises: 0-100% linoleic acid; 0-100% oleic acid; 

 0-10% polyunsaturated fatty acids; and wherein the adipose mimic composition does not contain palmitic or stearic acid and is liquid at room temperature. Claim 16. The MRI calibration object of Claim 15, wherein the adipose mimic composition comprises: between 0 and 18.7% linoleic acid Claim 17. The MRI calibration object of Claim 9, wherein the adipose mimic composition comprises: 9-10% linoleic acid; 80-90% oleic acid; and 0-10%. polyunsaturated fatty acids. Claim 18. The MRI calibration object of Claim 9, wherein the adipose mimic composition comprises: 9- 10% linoleic acid; 80-81 % oleic acid; and 9-10% polyunsaturated fatty acids. Claim 19. The MRI calibration object of Claim 9, wherein the adipose mimic composition comprises: 10- 50% of palmitic acid, stearic acid, or a combination of palmitic acid and stearic acid; and wherein the composition is solid at room temperature. Claim 20. The MRI calibration object of Claim 19, wherein the adipose mimic composition comprises: 62% linoleic acid; 25% oleic acid of 90% purity; 10% palmitic acid; and 3% stearic acid; and wherein the fatty acids of the composition are of 90-99% purity. Claim 21 . The MRI calibration object of Claim 19, wherein the adipose mimic composition comprises: 23% linoleic acid; 49% oleic acid; 22% palmitic acid; and wherein the fatty acids of the composition are of 90-99% purity. Claim 22. A method of assessing the accuracy of an MRI system, comprising the steps of obtaining an MRI scan of an aliquot of adipose mimic composition, under selected scan parameters, wherein the scan obtains a measurement of the value of one or more MRI property of the adipose mimic composition, wherein the adipose mimic composition comprises 0-100% linoleic acid, 0-100% oleic acid, 0-50% palmitic acid, 0-50% stearic acid, and 0-10% polyunsaturated fatty acids; and wherein the value of one or more selected MRI property of the adipose mimic composition, under the selected scan parameters, is known; 

 calculating a discrepancy value for the one or more MRI property of the adipose composition by comparing the one or more measured value to the known value. Claim 23. The method of Claim 22, wherein the MRI property is selected from the T1 relaxation value, the T2 relaxation value, the magnetic susceptibility value, and the chemical shift artifact value. Claim 24. The method of Claim 22, wherein the adipose mimic composition comprises: between 0 and 18.7% linoleic acid Claim 25. The method of Claim 22, wherein the adipose mimic composition comprises: 9-10% linoleic acid; 80-90% oleic acid; and 0-10%. polyunsaturated fatty acids. Claim 26. The method of Claim 25, wherein the adipose mimic composition comprises: 9-10% linoleic acid; 80-81 % oleic acid; and 9-10% polyunsaturated fatty acids. Claim 27. The method of Claim 22, wherein 

 the adipose mimic composition comprises: 10-50% of palmitic acid, stearic acid, or a combination of palmitic acid and stearic acid; and wherein the composition is solid at room temperature. Claim 28. The method of Claim 27, wherein the adipose mimic composition comprises: 62% linoleic acid; 25% oleic acid; 10% palmitic acid; and 3% stearic acid; and wherein the fatty acids of the composition are of 90-99% purity. Claim 29. The method of Claim 27, wherein The adipose mimic composition comprises: 23% linoleic acid; 49% oleic acid; and 22% palmitic acid and wherein the fatty acids of the composition are of 90-99% purity. Claim 30. The method of Claim 22, comprising the further step of: adjusting the MRI system or scan parameters to correct for any observed discrepancy value. Claim 31 . The method of Claim 30, wherein 

 the adjustment is an action selected from the group consisting of: altering the MRI system components, altering the MRI system operations, or altering the algorithms applied in image construction.
